## Verification Session: 2026-03-25 (Phase 4 Slice 4.11 - Outbox Claim Recovery and Retry Hardening)

### Scope
- Harden outbox worker behavior for crash-recovery and bounded retries
- Keep authoritative money path untouched (ledger/balance semantics unchanged)
- Keep backward compatibility and avoid deployment/env config changes

### Changes Applied
- Added migration `V21__outbox_claim_recovery_and_retry.sql`:
  - added `outbox_events.processing_started_at` claim timestamp column
  - added indexes for stale-processing reclaim and failed-retry scanning
  - replaced `get_pending_outbox_events(...)` with bounded, claim-safe logic:
    - reclaim stale `PROCESSING` rows back to `PENDING`
    - include retryable `FAILED` rows with backoff and max retry controls
    - claim rows atomically using `FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`
- Updated `OutboxEventRepository`:
  - preserved existing `getPendingEvents(int limit)` API for compatibility
  - added overloaded `getPendingEvents(...)` with retry/backoff/reclaim parameters
  - cleared `processing_started_at` when marking `PROCESSED` or `FAILED`
- Updated `OutboxEventPublisher`:
  - now calls parameterized claim API with explicit constants (`MAX_RETRIES`, backoff, reclaim timeout)
  - improved retry attempt logging to show actual attempt number
- Expanded `OutboxPatternIntegrationTest`:
  - stale claim reclaim proof
  - failed-event retry-after-backoff proof
  - max-retry blocking proof
- Stabilized `OutboxKafkaProjectorE2EIntegrationTest`:
  - waits until projection is visible in both read models (`event_feed` and `notification_inbox`) before asserting

